{"cursor":"8759","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox military conflict |conflict=Jewish revolt against Heraclius\n|partof=the ByzantineâSassanid War of 602â628 |image = |date=614â629\n|place=Palaestina Prima |territory=Palaestina Prima temporarily annexed to the\nPersian Empire as the Sassanid Jewish Commonwealth, but abandoned by Persians\nwithin 5 years and surrendered back to the Byzantines in 625. |result= *Temporal\nrule of Persians and Jews over Palaestina *Mutual massacres of Christians and\nJews *Brief restoration of Byzantine rule 625â634 *Expulsion of Jews from the\nregion |combatant1=Byzantine Empire |combatant2=Sassanid Empire, Jewish\nallies |commander1=Emperor Heraclius Patriarch Zacharias Abba Modestus\n|commander2=Shahrbaraz Nehemiah ben Hushiel Benjamin of Tiberias\n|strength1=Greek contingent of Jerusalem Byzantine Army |strength2=Persian\nforces; 26,000 Jewish rebels |casualties1=Tens of thousands\n|casualties2=Tens of thousands }}\n\n\nThe 'revolt against [[Heraclius]]' was a Jewish insurrection against the\nByzantine Empire across the Levant, coming to the aid of the Sassanid Persia\nduring the ByzantineâSassanid War of 602â628. The revolt began with the Battle\nof Antioch (613) and culminated with the conquest of Jerusalem in 614 by Persian\nand Jewish forces and the establishment of Jewish autonomy. The revolt ended\nwith the departure of the Persian troops and an eventual surrender of Jewish\nrebels to the Byzantines in the year 625 (or 628).\n","linknr":208,"url":"Jewish_revolt_against_Heraclius","recorded":1375061057,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Jewish_revolt_against_Heraclius&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Jewish_revolt_against_Heraclius&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.ph